{
  "stem": "13817.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And for that, we would then get food from the miner again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "To substitute extra food, this is one way I was doing it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We did same with the shoes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then we would say we lost it or somebody stole it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You knew you would get a whipping from the guards, but there was the choice, either food or-- or dying.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The same we would-- these miners there were-- at home didn't have any electricity.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They would use the carbide which was in the lamps to light their house, so we would sell the carbide to them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And-- in front of the elevator down in the shaft down where we were working, there was a big pile of used-up carbide.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We would go through the pile and pick out all the little pieces and put them in our lamp and would sell the big pieces for food.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Sometimes--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes we would even sell the lamp and exchange the lamp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His was broken and we would bring it to camp and say, well, the lamp isn't working right.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Each lamp had a-- a little chain on it with a number, so you would switch the numbers over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this way, any which way you could, you would sell and try extra food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Also, what we would do is I would call it a-- a kind of sabotage.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody was organizing it, just a feeling for yourselves to get-- to get-- feel better.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We would mix the rocks with the coal.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We would-- there-- there was some places where you needed winches to lead the-- the coal wagons down steep hills from one level to the other.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
